Rating: 0
Advice to the cook from Sunnyvale - I'm puzzled by your outcome. Perhaps your cut of meat was not of high quality - I just made a double batch of this with brisket from Whole Foods and it's exceptionally tender. Also, instead of thickening your sauce by adding cornstarch, you should reduce it over high heat after removing the solids. This both thickens and concentrates the flavors.

Rating: 2
I've only made Brisket one time before. This was a LOT of work, the flavor was pretty good, the meat wasn't very tender, the sauce was too thin (I thinckened it with cornstarch). Perhaps cooking it even longer would have worked out. I thought it was a LOT of chopping for the results I got.

Rating: 4
Delicious. After years of serving my own brisket creation, I tried this one in small-batch mode prior to Passover. It's quite nice. I had two bags of Trader Joe's chopped dates, so used some of those in lieu of whole ones. Other than that, followed as written and quite delighted with the result. Will be making 10 pounds of this this for 15 people next week.